msgctxt "dn10:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Long Discourses 10"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn10:2.1"
msgid "Subhasutta"
msgstr "With Subha"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts1.204"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn10:3.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme aciraparinibbute bhagavati."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Sāvatthī, in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. It was not long after the Buddha had become "
"finally extinguished."

msgctxt "dn10:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena subho māṇavo todeyyaputto sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati "
"kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the brahmin student Subha, Todeyya’s son, was residing in "
"Sāvatthī on some business."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto aññataraṃ māṇavakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then he addressed a certain student:"

msgctxt "dn10:4.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, māṇavaka, yena samaṇo ānando tenupasaṅkama;"
msgstr "“Here, student, go to the ascetic Ānanda"

msgctxt "dn10:4.3"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena samaṇaṃ ānandaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ "
"lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:"
msgstr ""
"and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and "
"well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably."

msgctxt "dn10:4.4"
msgid ""
"‘subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhavantaṃ ānandaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ "
"lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:4.5"
msgid "Evañca vadehi:"
msgstr "And then say: "

msgctxt "dn10:4.6"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu kira bhavaṃ ānando yena subhassa māṇavassa todeyyaputtassa nivesanaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, please visit the student Subha, Todeyya’s son, at his home out of "
"compassion.’”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.3"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1.205"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so māṇavako subhassa māṇavassa todeyyaputtassa paṭissutvā "
"yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied the student, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn10:5.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:5.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:5.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so māṇavako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:5.5"
msgid ""
"“subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhavantaṃ ānandaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ "
"lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:5.6"
msgid "evañca vadeti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:5.7"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu kira bhavaṃ ānando yena subhassa māṇavassa todeyyaputtassa nivesanaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando taṃ māṇavakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoke, Venerable Ānanda said to him:"

msgctxt "dn10:6.2"
msgid "“akālo kho, māṇavaka."
msgstr "“It’s not the right time, student."

msgctxt "dn10:6.3"
msgid "Atthi me ajja bhesajjamattā pītā."
msgstr "I’ve drunk sufficient refreshments for today."

msgctxt "dn10:6.4"
msgid "Appevanāma svepi upasaṅkameyyāma kālañca samayañca upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "But hopefully tomorrow I’ll get a chance to visit him.” "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so māṇavako āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena "
"subho māṇavo todeyyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied the student. he went back to Subha, and told him what "
"had happened, adding:"

msgctxt "dn10:7.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā subhaṃ māṇavaṃ todeyyaputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.3"
msgid "“avocumhā kho mayaṃ bhoto vacanena taṃ bhavantaṃ ānandaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhavantaṃ ānandaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ "
"lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati, evañca vadeti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.5"
msgid ""
"“sādhu kira bhavaṃ ānando yena subhassa māṇavassa todeyyaputtassa nivesanaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bho, samaṇo ānando maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.7"
msgid "‘akālo kho, māṇavaka."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.8"
msgid "Atthi me ajja bhesajjamattā pītā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.9"
msgid "Appevanāma svepi upasaṅkameyyāma kālañca samayañca upādāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:7.10"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatāpi kho, bho, katameva etaṃ, yato kho so bhavaṃ ānando okāsamakāsi "
"svātanāyapi upasaṅkamanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This much, sir, I managed to do. At least Master Ānanda will take the "
"opportunity to visit tomorrow.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:8.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā "
"pattacīvaramādāya cetakena bhikkhunā pacchāsamaṇena yena subhassa māṇavassa "
"todeyyaputtassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then when the night had passed, Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking "
"his bowl and robes, went with Venerable Cetaka as his second monk to Subha’s "
"home,"

msgctxt "dn10:8.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.206"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Subha went up to Ānanda,"

msgctxt "dn10:9.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "dn10:9.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "dn10:9.4"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn10:9.5"
msgid ""
"“bhavañhi ānando tassa bhoto gotamassa dīgharattaṃ upaṭṭhāko santikāvacaro "
"samīpacārī."
msgstr ""
"“Master Ānanda, you were Master Gotama’s attendant. You were close to him, "
"living in his presence."

msgctxt "dn10:9.6"
msgid ""
"Bhavametaṃ ānando jāneyya, yesaṃ so bhavaṃ gotamo dhammānaṃ vaṇṇavādī ahosi, "
"yattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr ""
"You ought to know what things Master Gotama praised, and in which he "
"encouraged, settled, and grounded all these people."

msgctxt "dn10:9.7"
msgid ""
"Katamesānaṃ kho, bho ānanda, dhammānaṃ so bhavaṃ gotamo vaṇṇavādī ahosi;"
msgstr "What were those things?”"

msgctxt "dn10:9.8"
msgid "kattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:10.1"
msgid "“Tiṇṇaṃ kho, māṇava, khandhānaṃ so bhagavā vaṇṇavādī ahosi;"
msgstr ""
"“Student, the Buddha praised three sets of things, and that’s what he "
"encouraged, settled, and grounded all these people in."

msgctxt "dn10:10.2"
msgid "ettha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:10.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "dn10:10.4"
msgid ""
"Ariyassa sīlakkhandhassa, ariyassa samādhikkhandhassa, ariyassa "
"paññākkhandhassa."
msgstr "The entire spectrum of noble ethics, immersion, and wisdom."

msgctxt "dn10:10.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, māṇava, tiṇṇaṃ khandhānaṃ so bhagavā vaṇṇavādī ahosi;"
msgstr "These are the three sets of things that the Buddha praised.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn10:10.6"
msgid "ettha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesī”ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn10:11.1"
msgid "1. Sīlakkhandha"
msgstr "The Entire Spectrum of Ethics"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana so, bho ānanda, ariyo sīlakkhandho, yassa so bhavaṃ gotamo "
"vaṇṇavādī ahosi, yattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesī”ti?"
msgstr "“But what was that noble spectrum of ethics that the Buddha praised?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, māṇava, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā "
"devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā."
msgstr ""
"“Student, it’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the "
"world, supreme trainer of people, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, "
"blessed."

msgctxt "dn10:13.2"
msgid ""
"So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ "
"sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti."
msgstr ""
"He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and "
"Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and "
"he makes it known to others."

msgctxt "dn10:13.3"
msgid ""
"So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ "
"sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches Dharma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice "
"that’s entirely full and pure."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:13.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule "
"paccājāto."
msgstr ""
"A householder hears that Dharma, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn "
"in some clan."

msgctxt "dn10:13.5"
msgid "So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati."
msgstr "They gain faith in the Realized One,"

msgctxt "dn10:13.6"
msgid "So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "and reflect:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn10:13.7"
msgid ""
"‘sambādho gharāvāso rajopatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ "
"ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ "
"carituṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is "
"wide open. It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual "
"life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell."

msgctxt "dn10:13.8"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ochre robes, and go forth "
"from the lay life into homelessness?’"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:13.9"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā "
"bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā "
"ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati."
msgstr ""
"After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small "
"family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ochre robes, and go "
"forth from the lay life into homelessness."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:13.10"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati, "
"ācāragocarasampanno, anumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu, kāyakammavacīkammena samannāgato kusalena, parisuddhājīvo, "
"sīlasampanno, indriyesu guttadvāro, satisampajaññena samannāgato, santuṭṭho."
msgstr ""
"Once they’ve gone forth, they live restrained in the code of conduct, with "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. They act skillfully "
"by body and speech. They’re purified in livelihood and accomplished in "
"ethical conduct. They guard the sense doors, have mindfulness and "
"situational awareness, and are content."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:14.1"
msgid "Kathañca, māṇava, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant accomplished in ethics?"

msgctxt "dn10:14.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, "
"nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant gives up killing living creatures. They renounce "
"violence and harming. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion "
"for all creatures. …"

msgctxt "dn10:14.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, "
"nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: sīlasmiṃ → athā sāmañ­ña­phala­sutte 194 yāva 210 anucchedesu evaṃ
msgctxt "dn10:14.4"
msgid "idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:15.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn10:15.2"
msgid ""
"santikammaṃ paṇidhikammaṃ bhūtakammaṃ bhūrikammaṃ vassakammaṃ vossakammaṃ "
"vatthukammaṃ vatthuparikammaṃ ācamanaṃ nhāpanaṃ juhanaṃ vamanaṃ virecanaṃ "
"uddhaṃvirecanaṃ adhovirecanaṃ sīsavirecanaṃ kaṇṇatelaṃ nettatappanaṃ "
"natthukammaṃ añjanaṃ paccañjanaṃ sālākiyaṃ sallakattiyaṃ dārakatikicchā "
"mūlabhesajjānaṃ anuppadānaṃ osadhīnaṃ paṭimokkho iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes rites for propitiation, for fulfilling wishes, for ghosts, for "
"the earth, for rain, for property settlement, and for preparing and "
"consecrating house sites, and those involving rinsing and bathing, and "
"oblations. It also includes administering emetics, purgatives, expectorants "
"and phlegmagogues; administering ear-oils, eye restoratives, nasal medicine, "
"ointments and counter-ointments; surgery with needle and scalpel, treating "
"children, prescribing root medicines, and binding on herbs. They refrain "
"from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood. …"

msgctxt "dn10:15.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni "
"bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ "
"kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:15.4"
msgid "santikammaṃ paṇidhikammaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:15.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:15.6"
msgid ""
"osadhīnaṃ paṭimokkho iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā "
"paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:15.7"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.29"></a>
#. VAR: Sa kho so → ayaṃ kho so (mr)
msgctxt "dn10:16.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, māṇava, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno na kutoci bhayaṃ samanupassati, "
"yadidaṃ sīlasaṃvarato."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant thus accomplished in ethics sees no danger in any quarter in "
"regards to their ethical restraint."

msgctxt "dn10:16.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto nihatapaccāmitto na kutoci "
"bhayaṃ samanupassati, yadidaṃ paccatthikato;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a king who has defeated his enemies. He sees no danger from his "
"foes in any quarter."

msgctxt "dn10:16.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno na kutoci bhayaṃ "
"samanupassati, yadidaṃ sīlasaṃvarato."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant thus accomplished in ethics sees no danger in any quarter in "
"regards to their ethical restraint."

msgctxt "dn10:16.4"
msgid ""
"So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a "
"blameless happiness inside themselves."

msgctxt "dn10:16.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, māṇava, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.30"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:17.1"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho so, māṇava, ariyo sīlakkhandho yassa so bhagavā vaṇṇavādī ahosi, "
"yattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr "This is that noble spectrum of ethics that the Buddha praised."

msgctxt "dn10:17.2"
msgid "Atthi cevettha uttarikaraṇīyan”ti."
msgstr "But there is still more to be done.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.207"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:18.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing,"

msgctxt "dn10:18.2"
msgid "So cāyaṃ, bho ānanda, ariyo sīlakkhandho paripuṇṇo, no aparipuṇṇo."
msgstr "This noble spectrum of ethics is complete, not lacking anything!"

msgctxt "dn10:18.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ paripuṇṇañcāhaṃ, bho ānanda, ariyaṃ sīlakkhandhaṃ ito bahiddhā aññesu "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇesu na samanupassāmi."
msgstr ""
"Such a complete spectrum of ethics cannot be seen among the other ascetics "
"and brahmins."

msgctxt "dn10:18.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ paripuṇṇañca, bho ānanda, ariyaṃ sīlakkhandhaṃ ito bahiddhā aññe "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā attani samanupasseyyuṃ, te tāvatakeneva attamanā assu:"
msgstr ""
"Were other ascetics and brahmins to see such a complete spectrum of noble "
"ethics in themselves, they’d be delighted with just that much:"

msgctxt "dn10:18.5"
msgid ""
"‘alamettāvatā, katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci "
"uttarikaraṇīyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘At this point it’s enough; at this point our work is done. We’ve reached "
"the goal of our ascetic life. There is nothing more to do done.’"

msgctxt "dn10:18.6"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhavaṃ ānando evamāha:"
msgstr "And yet you say:"

msgctxt "dn10:18.7"
msgid "‘atthi cevettha uttarikaraṇīyan’”ti."
msgstr "‘But there is still more to be done.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn10:19.1"
msgid "2. Samādhikkhandha"
msgstr "The Spectrum of Immersion"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.1"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana so, bho ānanda, ariyo samādhikkhandho, yassa so bhavaṃ gotamo "
"vaṇṇavādī ahosi, yattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what was that noble spectrum of immersion that the Buddha praised?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:21.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, māṇava, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "“And how, student, does a mendicant guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "dn10:21.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī;"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "dn10:21.3"
msgid ""
"yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight was left unrestrained, bad unwholesome qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn10:21.4"
msgid ""
"tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ "
"āpajjati."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn10:21.5"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

msgctxt "dn10:21.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:21.7"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

msgctxt "dn10:21.8"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

msgctxt "dn10:21.9"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

msgctxt "dn10:21.10"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī;"
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details. "

msgctxt "dn10:21.11"
msgid ""
"yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of the mind was left unrestrained, bad unwholesome qualities "
"of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of the mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "dn10:21.12"
msgid ""
"tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ "
"āpajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:21.13"
msgid ""
"So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied "
"bliss inside themselves."

msgctxt "dn10:21.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, māṇava, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant guards the sense doors. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:22.1"
msgid "Kathañca, māṇava, bhikkhu satisampajaññena samannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have mindfulness and situational awareness?"

msgctxt "dn10:22.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite "
"vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, "
"saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite "
"sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite "
"nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and "
"coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the "
"limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, "
"chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, "
"sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent."

msgctxt "dn10:22.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, māṇava, bhikkhu satisampajaññena samannāgato hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has mindfulness and situational awareness."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:23.1"
msgid "Kathañca, māṇava, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant content?"

msgctxt "dn10:23.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena "
"kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-"
"food to look after the belly."

msgctxt "dn10:23.3"
msgid "So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati."
msgstr "Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things."

msgctxt "dn10:23.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti, sapattabhārova ḍeti;"
msgstr "They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden."

msgctxt "dn10:23.5"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena "
"kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body "
"and alms-food to look after the belly."

msgctxt "dn10:23.6"
msgid "So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati."
msgstr "Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things."

msgctxt "dn10:23.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, māṇava, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is content."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:24.1"
msgid ""
"So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena "
"indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato, "
"imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ "
"rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ "
"palālapuñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, "
"and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness, and this noble "
"contentment, they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a "
"tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the "
"open air, a heap of straw."

msgctxt "dn10:24.2"
msgid ""
"So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ "
"kāyaṃ paṇidhāya, parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down in the meditation "
"posture with their body erect, and establish mindfulness right there."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:25.1"
msgid ""
"So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati abhijjhāya cittaṃ "
"parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, "
"cleansing the mind of desire."

msgctxt "dn10:25.2"
msgid ""
"Byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī "
"byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill "
"will, full of compassion for all creatures, cleansing the mind of ill will."

msgctxt "dn10:25.3"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, "
"thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness "
"and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of "
"dullness and drowsiness."

msgctxt "dn10:25.4"
msgid ""
"Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto "
"uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, "
"their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse."

msgctxt "dn10:25.5"
msgid ""
"Vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṅkathī kusalesu dhammesu, "
"vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about "
"wholesome qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:26.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso iṇaṃ ādāya kammante payojeyya."
msgstr "Suppose a man who has gotten into debt were to apply himself to work,"

msgctxt "dn10:26.2"
msgid "Tassa te kammantā samijjheyyuṃ."
msgstr "and his efforts proved successful."

msgctxt "dn10:26.3"
msgid ""
"So yāni ca porāṇāni iṇamūlāni tāni ca byantiṃ kareyya, siyā cassa uttariṃ "
"avasiṭṭhaṃ dārabharaṇāya."
msgstr ""
"He would pay off the original loan and have enough left over to support his "
"partner."

msgctxt "dn10:26.4"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn10:26.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho pubbe iṇaṃ ādāya kammante payojesiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:26.6"
msgid "Tassa me te kammantā samijjhiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:26.7"
msgid ""
"Sohaṃ yāni ca porāṇāni iṇamūlāni tāni ca byantiṃ akāsiṃ, atthi ca me uttariṃ "
"avasiṭṭhaṃ dārabharaṇāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:26.8"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "he’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:27.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso ābādhiko assa dukkhito bāḷhagilāno;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person who was sick, suffering, gravely ill. They’d lose "
"their appetite and get physically weak."

msgctxt "dn10:27.2"
msgid "bhattañcassa nacchādeyya, na cassa kāye balamattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:27.3"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena tamhā ābādhā mucceyya, bhattañcassa chādeyya, siyā cassa "
"kāye balamattā."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they’d recover from that illness, and regain their "
"appetite and their strength."

msgctxt "dn10:27.4"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn10:27.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho pubbe ābādhiko ahosiṃ dukkhito bāḷhagilāno, bhattañca me "
"nacchādesi, na ca me āsi kāye balamattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:27.6"
msgid ""
"Somhi etarahi tamhā ābādhā mutto bhattañca me chādeti, atthi ca me kāye "
"balamattā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:27.7"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:28.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso bandhanāgāre baddho assa."
msgstr "Suppose a person was imprisoned in a jail."

msgctxt "dn10:28.2"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena tamhā bandhanāgārā mucceyya sotthinā abbhayena, na cassa "
"kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they were released from jail, safe and sound, with no "
"loss of wealth."

msgctxt "dn10:28.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn10:28.4"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho pubbe bandhanāgāre baddho ahosiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:28.5"
msgid ""
"Somhi etarahi tamhā bandhanāgārā mutto sotthinā abbhayena, natthi ca me "
"kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:28.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:29.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso dāso assa anattādhīno parādhīno na yenakāmaṅgamo."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was a bondservant. They belonged to someone else and were "
"unable to go where they wish."

msgctxt "dn10:29.2"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena tamhā dāsabyā mucceyya, attādhīno aparādhīno bhujisso "
"yenakāmaṅgamo."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they were freed from bondage. They’d belong to "
"themselves, an emancipated individual able to go where they wish."

msgctxt "dn10:29.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn10:29.4"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho pubbe dāso ahosiṃ anattādhīno parādhīno na yenakāmaṅgamo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:29.5"
msgid ""
"Somhi etarahi tamhā dāsabyā mutto attādhīno aparādhīno bhujisso "
"yenakāmaṅgamo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:29.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:30.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso sadhano sabhogo kantāraddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya "
"dubbhikkhaṃ sappaṭibhayaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person with wealth and property who was travelling along "
"a desert road, which was perilous, with nothing to eat."

msgctxt "dn10:30.2"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena taṃ kantāraṃ nitthareyya, sotthinā gāmantaṃ anupāpuṇeyya "
"khemaṃ appaṭibhayaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they crossed over the desert safely, reaching the "
"neighborhood of a village, a sanctuary free of peril."

msgctxt "dn10:30.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn10:30.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho pubbe sadhano sabhogo kantāraddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjiṃ dubbhikkhaṃ "
"sappaṭibhayaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: etarahi taṃ kantāraṃ → etarahi kantāraṃ (c1)
msgctxt "dn10:30.5"
msgid ""
"Somhi etarahi taṃ kantāraṃ nitthiṇṇo, sotthinā gāmantaṃ anuppatto khemaṃ "
"appaṭibhayan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:30.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:31.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu yathā iṇaṃ yathā rogaṃ yathā bandhanāgāraṃ "
"yathā dāsabyaṃ yathā kantāraddhānamaggaṃ, evaṃ ime pañca nīvaraṇe appahīne "
"attani samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, as long as these five hindrances are not given up inside "
"themselves, a mendicant regards them as a debt, a disease, a prison, "
"slavery, and a desert crossing."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:32.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, yathā āṇaṇyaṃ yathā ārogyaṃ yathā bandhanāmokkhaṃ yathā "
"bhujissaṃ yathā khemantabhūmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"But when these five hindrances are given up inside themselves, a mendicant "
"regards this as freedom from debt, good health, release from prison, "
"emancipation, and sanctuary."

#. VAR: Evameva kho → evameva (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "dn10:32.2"
msgid "Evameva kho bhikkhu ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahīne attani samanupassati."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:33.1"
msgid ""
"Tassime pañca nīvaraṇe pahīne attani samanupassato pāmojjaṃ jāyati, "
"pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ "
"vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing that the hindrances have been given up in them, gladness springs up. "
"Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, the body "
"becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. And when "
"blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:34.1"
msgid ""
"So vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ "
"vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unwholesome qualities, "
"they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion, while applying the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn10:34.2"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born "
"of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.14"></a>
#. VAR: sanneyya → sandeyya (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "dn10:35.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, dakkho nhāpako vā nhāpakantevāsī vā kaṃsathāle "
"nhānīyacuṇṇāni ākiritvā udakena paripphosakaṃ paripphosakaṃ sanneyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s like when a skilled bathroom attendant or their apprentice pours bath "
"powder into a bronze dish, sprinkling it little by little with water. They "
"knead it"

msgctxt "dn10:35.2"
msgid ""
"Sāyaṃ nhānīyapiṇḍi snehānugatā snehaparetā santarabāhirā phuṭā snehena, na "
"ca paggharaṇī."
msgstr ""
"until the ball of bath powder is soaked and saturated with moisture, spread "
"through inside and out; yet no moisture oozes out."

msgctxt "dn10:35.3"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena "
"abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato "
"kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of seclusion."

msgctxt "dn10:35.4"
msgid ""
"Yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:35.5"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:35.6"
msgid "Idampissa hoti samādhismiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:36.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, māṇava, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the applying of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and "
"confidence, and unified mind, without applying the mind and keeping it "
"connected. "

msgctxt "dn10:36.2"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born "
"of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and "
"bliss born of immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.16"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts1.208"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:37.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, māṇava, udakarahado gambhīro ubbhidodako."
msgstr ""
"It’s like a deep lake fed by spring water. There’s no inlet to the east, "
"west, north, or south, and no rainfall to replenish it from time to time. "

msgctxt "dn10:37.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa nevassa puratthimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na dakkhiṇāya disāya "
"udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na pacchimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na uttarāya "
"disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, devo ca na kālena kālaṃ sammā dhāraṃ "
"anupaveccheyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:37.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tamhāva udakarahadā sītā vāridhārā ubbhijjitvā tameva udakarahadaṃ "
"sītena vārinā abhisandeyya parisandeyya paripūreyya paripphareyya, nāssa "
"kiñci sabbāvato udakarahadassa sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ assa."
msgstr ""
"But the stream of cool water welling up in the lake drenches, steeps, fills, "
"and spreads throughout the lake. There’s no part of the lake that’s not "
"spread through with cool water."

msgctxt "dn10:37.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion."

msgctxt "dn10:37.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:37.6"
msgid "yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:37.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:37.8"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:37.9"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:37.10"
msgid "Idampissa hoti samādhismiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:38.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, māṇava, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato "
"sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains "
"in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and "
"aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss’. "

msgctxt "dn10:38.2"
msgid "‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:38.3"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with bliss free of rapture. "
"There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:39.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā "
"appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake "
"saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni antonimuggaposīni, tāni yāva caggā yāva ca mūlā "
"sītena vārinā abhisannāni parisannāni paripūrāni paripphuṭāni, nāssa kiñci "
"sabbāvataṃ uppalānaṃ vā padumānaṃ vā puṇḍarīkānaṃ vā sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ "
"assa."
msgstr ""
"It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of "
"them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving "
"underwater. From the tip to the root they’re drenched, steeped, filled, and "
"soaked with cool water. There’s no part of them that’s not soaked with cool "
"water."

msgctxt "dn10:39.2"
msgid "Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion."

msgctxt "dn10:39.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:39.4"
msgid "yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:39.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:39.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:39.7"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:39.8"
msgid "Idampissa hoti samādhismiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.18"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:40.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, māṇava, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "dn10:40.2"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti;"
msgstr "They sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind."

msgctxt "dn10:40.3"
msgid ""
"nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr "There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:41.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso odātena vatthena sasīsaṃ pārupitvā nisinno assa, "
"nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa odātena vatthena apphuṭaṃ assa."
msgstr ""
"It’s like someone sitting wrapped from head to foot with white cloth. There’"
"s no part of the body that’s not spread over with white cloth."

msgctxt "dn10:41.2"
msgid "Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion."

msgctxt "dn10:41.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:41.4"
msgid ""
"yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:41.5"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:41.6"
msgid ""
"nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:41.7"
msgid "Idampissa hoti samādhismiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:42.1"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho so, māṇava, ariyo samādhikkhandho yassa so bhagavā vaṇṇavādī ahosi, "
"yattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr "This is that noble spectrum of immersion that the Buddha praised."

msgctxt "dn10:42.2"
msgid "Atthi cevettha uttarikaraṇīyan”ti."
msgstr "But there is still more to be done.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:43.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "dn10:43.2"
msgid "So cāyaṃ, bho ānanda, ariyo samādhikkhandho paripuṇṇo, no aparipuṇṇo."
msgstr "This noble spectrum of immersion is complete, not lacking anything!"

msgctxt "dn10:43.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ paripuṇṇañcāhaṃ, bho ānanda, ariyaṃ samādhikkhandhaṃ ito bahiddhā "
"aññesu samaṇabrāhmaṇesu na samanupassāmi."
msgstr ""
"Such a complete spectrum of immersion cannot be seen among the other "
"ascetics and brahmins."

msgctxt "dn10:43.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ paripuṇṇañca, bho ānanda, ariyaṃ samādhikkhandhaṃ ito bahiddhā aññe "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā attani samanupasseyyuṃ, te tāvatakeneva attamanā assu:"
msgstr ""
"Were other ascetics and brahmins to see such a complete spectrum of noble "
"immersion in themselves, they’d be delighted with just that much:"

msgctxt "dn10:43.5"
msgid ""
"‘alamettāvatā, katamettāvatā, anuppatto no sāmaññattho, natthi no kiñci "
"uttarikaraṇīyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘At this point it’s enough; at this point our work is done. We’ve reached "
"the goal of our ascetic life. There is nothing more to do done.’"

msgctxt "dn10:43.6"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhavaṃ ānando evamāha:"
msgstr "And yet you say:"

msgctxt "dn10:43.7"
msgid "‘atthi cevettha uttarikaraṇīyan’ti."
msgstr "‘But there is still more to be done.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn10:44.1"
msgid "3. Paññākkhandha"
msgstr "The Spectrum of Wisdom"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.20"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:45.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo pana so, bho ānanda, ariyo paññākkhandho, yassa bho bhavaṃ gotamo "
"vaṇṇavādī ahosi, yattha ca imaṃ janataṃ samādapesi nivesesi patiṭṭhāpesī”ti?"
msgstr "“But what was that noble spectrum of wisdom that the Buddha praised?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.21"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:46.1"
msgid ""
"“So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"“When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward knowledge and vision."

msgctxt "dn10:46.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "dn10:46.3"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho me kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo "
"odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo;"
msgstr ""
"‘This body of mine is physical. It’s made up of the four primary elements, "
"produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to "
"impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction."

msgctxt "dn10:46.4"
msgid "idañca pana me viññāṇaṃ ettha sitaṃ ettha paṭibaddhan’ti."
msgstr "And this consciousness of mine is attached to it, tied to it.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.22"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts1.209"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:47.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato "
"accho vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, "
"with expert workmanship, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all "
"good qualities. "

msgctxt "dn10:47.2"
msgid ""
"Tatrāssa suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"And it was strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown."

msgctxt "dn10:47.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso hatthe karitvā paccavekkheyya:"
msgstr ""
"And someone with good eyesight were to take it in their hand and examine it:"

msgctxt "dn10:47.4"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho "
"vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno."
msgstr ""
"‘This beryl gem is naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, with expert "
"workmanship, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all good "
"qualities. "

msgctxt "dn10:47.5"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ "
"vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And it’s strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown.’"

msgctxt "dn10:47.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte "
"ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward knowledge and vision."

msgctxt "dn10:47.7"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.8"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho me kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo "
"odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.9"
msgid "Idañca pana me viññāṇaṃ ettha sitaṃ ettha paṭibaddhan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.10"
msgid "Yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.12"
msgid "āneñjappatte ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.13"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.14"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.15"
msgid "ettha paṭibaddhanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:47.16"
msgid "Idampissa hoti paññāya."
msgstr "This pertains to their wisdom."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:48.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte manomayaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimmānāya cittaṃ "
"abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward the creation of a mind-made body."

msgctxt "dn10:48.2"
msgid ""
"So imamhā kāyā aññaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimmināti rūpiṃ manomayaṃ sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ "
"ahīnindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"From this body they create another body, physical, mind-made, complete in "
"all its various parts, not deficient in any faculty."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:49.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, māṇava, puriso muñjamhā īsikaṃ pavāheyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person was to draw a reed out from its sheath."

msgctxt "dn10:49.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn10:49.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ muñjo ayaṃ īsikā;"
msgstr ""
"‘This is the reed, this is the sheath. The reed and the sheath are different "
"things. The reed has been drawn out from the sheath.’"

msgctxt "dn10:49.4"
msgid "añño muñjo aññā īsikā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.5"
msgid "muñjamhā tveva īsikā pavāḷhā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.6"
msgid "Seyyathā vā pana, māṇava, puriso asiṃ kosiyā pavāheyya."
msgstr "Or suppose a person was to draw a sword out from its scabbard."

msgctxt "dn10:49.7"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn10:49.8"
msgid "‘ayaṃ asi, ayaṃ kosi;"
msgstr ""
"‘This is the sword, this is the scabbard. The sword and the scabbard are "
"different things. The sword has been drawn out from the scabbard.’"

msgctxt "dn10:49.9"
msgid "añño asi, aññā kosi;"
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn10:49.10"
msgid "kosiyā tveva asi pavāḷho’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn10:49.11"
msgid "Seyyathā vā pana, māṇava, puriso ahiṃ karaṇḍā uddhareyya."
msgstr "Or suppose a person was to draw a snake out from its slough."

msgctxt "dn10:49.12"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn10:49.13"
msgid "‘ayaṃ ahi, ayaṃ karaṇḍo;"
msgstr ""
"‘This is the snake, this is the slough. The snake and the slough are "
"different things. The snake has been drawn out from the slough.’"

msgctxt "dn10:49.14"
msgid "añño ahi, añño karaṇḍo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.15"
msgid "karaṇḍā tveva ahi ubbhato’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.16"
msgid "Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward the creation of a mind-made body."

msgctxt "dn10:49.17"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.18"
msgid ""
"yampi, māṇava, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe "
"vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte manomayaṃ kāyaṃ "
"abhinimmānāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.19"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:49.20"
msgid "Idampissa hoti paññāya."
msgstr "This pertains to their wisdom."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.25"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:50.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte iddhividhāya cittaṃ abhinīharati "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward psychic power."

msgctxt "dn10:50.2"
msgid "So anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—"
msgstr "They wield the many kinds of psychic power:"

msgctxt "dn10:50.3"
msgid "ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti;"
msgstr "multiplying themselves and becoming one again; "

msgctxt "dn10:50.4"
msgid ""
"āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati "
"seyyathāpi ākāse;"
msgstr ""
"going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space;"
" "

msgctxt "dn10:50.5"
msgid "pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake;"
msgstr "diving in and out of the earth as if it was water; "

msgctxt "dn10:50.6"
msgid "udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ;"
msgstr "walking on water as if it was earth; "

msgctxt "dn10:50.7"
msgid "ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo;"
msgstr "flying cross-legged through the air like a bird;"

msgctxt "dn10:50.8"
msgid ""
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃ mahiddhike evaṃ mahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati "
"parimajjati;"
msgstr ""
"touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful;"

msgctxt "dn10:50.9"
msgid "yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.26"></a>
msgctxt "dn10:51.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, māṇava, dakkho kumbhakāro vā kumbhakārantevāsī vā "
"suparikammakatāya mattikāya yaññadeva bhājanavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya, taṃ tadeva "
"kareyya abhinipphādeyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there an expert potter or their apprentice had some well-prepared "
"clay. They could produce any kind of pot that they like."

msgctxt "dn10:51.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathā vā pana, māṇava, dakkho dantakāro vā dantakārantevāsī vā "
"suparikammakatasmiṃ dantasmiṃ yaññadeva dantavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya, taṃ tadeva "
"kareyya abhinipphādeyya."
msgstr ""
"Or suppose there an expert ivory-carver or their apprentice had some well-"
"prepared ivory. They could produce any kind of ivory item that they like."

msgctxt "dn10:51.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathā vā pana, māṇava, dakkho suvaṇṇakāro vā suvaṇṇakārantevāsī vā "
"suparikammakatasmiṃ suvaṇṇasmiṃ yaññadeva suvaṇṇavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya, taṃ "
"tadeva kareyya abhinipphādeyya."
msgstr ""
"Or suppose an expert goldsmith or their apprentice had some well-prepared "
"gold. They could produce any kind of gold item that they like."

msgctxt "dn10:51.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, māṇava, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward psychic power."

msgctxt "dn10:51.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn10:51.6"
msgid ""
"yampi māṇava bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe "
"vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte iddhividhāya cittaṃ "
"abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""

